  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>sweet <span class=\"text-highlight\">potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></span></strong><span class=\"text-highlight\"> (</span>skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Place the<strong> sweet potato</strong> on a baking tray, drizzle with <span class=\"text-highlight\">1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span></span><strong>olive oil</strong> and season generously with<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Put them in the oven for 30 min or until crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock cube<span style=\"color:#e86754;\">[s]</span></strong> with 800ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Peel and dice the<strong> brown onion<span style=\"color:#e86754;\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add <span class=\"text-highlight\">1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span></span><strong> olive oil</strong> to a large pan over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3 min until soft but not coloured</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>arborio</strong> <strong>rice</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> into the softened <strong>onion</strong> </p>\n<p>Add <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>1/3</strong> </span>of the <strong>stock</strong> and stir continuously with a wooden spoon until it's absorbed</p>\n<p>Continue to add the stock a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 15-20 min, until all the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>pecans</strong> to the sweet potato tray and put it back in the oven for 5 min or until they have slightly darkened in colour</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>sage</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>pecans</strong> coarsely</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>sage</strong> and <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>3/4</strong></span> of the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>sweet potato</strong> to the risotto</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/283.step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>cooked</strong></span> <strong>risotto</strong> from the heat and crumble in <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>half</strong></span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [all]</span> the <strong>blue cheese </strong><span class=\"text-highlight\">(save the rest for another time)</span>, stirring through until melted</p>\n<p>Serve in bowls and top with the <strong>remaining sweet potato</strong> and <strong>chopped pecans</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
